IBADAN – Lead Investigator of the Nigerian Site on REaCH Project, Professor Akinyinka Omigbodun has appealed to the Oyo State Government to make budget provisions for the adoption and the use of remote consulting to increase access to healthcare, particularly for the chronic disease population in the state. Professor Omigbodun stated this at a two-day dissemination workshop organised for healthcare providers and policy actors on the key findings of the project towards encouraging the adoption and use to improve access to health care in the state. Omigbodun is a Professor of Obstetrics and Gynaecology at the College of the Medicine University of Ibadan and Lead Investigator for the Nigeria Site on the Project “COVID-19: Determining trustworthiness and safety of REmote consulting in primary Health care for chronic disease population in Africa” funded by UK Research and Innovation, Global Challenges Research Fund and Newton Fund (UKRI GCRF/Newton Fund). The Project’s Principal investigator is Professor Jackie Sturt at King’s College in the UK while Professor Eme Owoaje and Dr Olufunke Fayehun are co-investigators for the Nigerian Site.